Edit {"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1784459807581/src/agentic_coding/web_research.rs","old_string":"    let open = uncovered_aspects(query, progress);
    // A refinement has to actually refine. Nothing uncovered means the question
    // is answered; *everything* uncovered means the evidence bears on none of it
    // — usually because the sources answer in another language than the question
    // was asked in — and re-issuing the same terms would return the same pages.
    // Requiring a proper subset rules both out, and makes the loop terminate on
    // its own: uncovered aspects only ever shrink as evidence accumulates.
    if open.is_empty() || open.len() >= aspects_of(query).len() {
        return None;
    }","new_string":"    let open = uncovered_aspects(query, progress);
    // A refinement has to actually refine, and the bar for spending another
    // round has to be high, because token coverage is a weak proxy for
    // "answered". A page that genuinely answers "when are elections in usa"
    // still will not repeat every word of the question, so a few uncovered
    // tokens are normal and must not trigger a second search.
    //
    // Another round is therefore justified only when the evidence covers most of
    // the question and leaves a distinct minority of it open — the shape of a
    // real follow-up, where the specs were found and only the warranty is
    // missing. At the other extreme, *everything* uncovered means the evidence
    // bears on none of the question, usually because the sources answer in a
    // different language than it was asked in; re-issuing those same terms would
    // return the same pages. Both extremes stop here.
    //
    // This also makes the loop terminate on its own, independently of the round
    // budget: uncovered aspects only ever shrink as evidence accumulates.
    if open.is_empty() || open.len() * 2 >= aspects_of(query).len() {
        return None;
    }"}

